node.text:
Pineapple Sriracha Shrimp Bowls that taste even better than they look! 🦐🍍🔥
.
Pineapple Sriracha Shrimp Bowls for the perfect sweet, spicy tang we all know and love. My good friends at @oklahomajoes just dropped a new grill, the Blackjack Kettle Charcoal Grill, which gave me the perfect opportunity to throw down on some shrimp bowls. I made a quick pineapple marinade for these shrimp and completed the meal with sriracha mayo and cilantro lime rice. Throw it all in a pineapple bowl for that extra wow factor. Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/pineapple-sriracha-shrimp-bowls/
. 
. 
.

node.text:
Scored & Grilled Boneless Beef Short Ribs over the fire today! 🥩 🔪 🌿 🔥
.
A few weeks back, one of my friends described to me the process of scoring meat like a hassleback potato. For more tough cuts like beef short ribs, it helps the marinade tenderize the meat more and give a larger surface area to get a nice crust. I scored these boneless beef short ribs and let them marinate overnight in a soy sauce, sriracha, rice wine vinegar, sesame seed oil and Korean BBQ seasoning mixture. Grilled them for 4-5 minutes per side and glazed with some fish sauce for an extra tang right at the end. I pulled them off around 130F. They were super tender and delicious! Highly recommend this technique! Find more recipes like this on my blog: www.overthefirecooking.com!🍻 👍
.
.
.
Steaks:
- 5-6 Boneless Beef Short Rib filets
- Fish Sauce, for glaze 
- Scallions, for garnish 
- Sesame Seeds, for garnish
.
Marinade:
- 2 tbsp of Korean BBQ Seasoning
- 1/2 cup of Soy Sauce 
- 1/4 cup of Rice Vinegar
- 2 Limes, juiced
- 2 tsp of Sesame Seed Oil
.
Instructions:
1. Take your beef ribs and score them across about 1/4 inch deep on both sides.
3. In a food safe bowl, add your beef and marinade. Mix and set in fridge for 4 hours or ideally overnight.
4. Preheat your grill to medium-high temperature (around 375F).
5. Add steaks to grill and cook for about 4-5 minutes per side or until they are 130F internal. Towards the end, glaze with fish sauce for a nice finishing crust.
6. Pull steak off once done and rest for 7-8 minutes. Top with scallions, sesame seeds and enjoy!
.
.
.

node.text:
Lemon Chili Bacon Wrapped Chicken Skewers over the fire 🍗 🥓 🍋 🌶 🔥
.
For a while now, I have been wanting to make this recipe. After seeing some South American cooks use bacon wrapped chicken on skewers, I knew that it was on the to do list sooner than later. Seasoned these guys with my own version of Peri Peri Sauce. This is a spicy citrus sauce that goes really well on chicken. It also cuts through the fat of the bacon nicely to make a savory, spicy and citrusy flavor. Grilled over a medium to medium-low fire to prevent flare ups, this Lemon Chili Bacon Wrapped Chicken Skewers were a bomb recipe for the backyard. Cheers! 🍻 👍
.
.
.
Ingredients:
.
Chicken Skewers:
- 2 lbs of Chicken Breast, cubed
- 18-20 Bacon Slices, cut in half
- Lemon juice, garnish
- Cilantro, garnish
.
Lemon Chili Sauce
- 2 Whole Habaneros
- 4-5 Garlic Cloves
- 1/8 cup of Cilantro
- 2 tbsp of White Vinegar
- 1 tbsp of Chipotle Powder
- 1 tbsp Dried Oregano
- 1 Lemon, juiced
- Oil, as needed
.
Steps:
- In a blender, mix the Lemon Chili sauce until smooth. Reverse 1/8 cup of sauce, then mix the rest over the chicken. Marinate for at least 2 hours or ideally overnight.
- Preheat grill for 3 zone cooking at medium heat (around 300F). - Wrap the chicken in bacon them securely skewer. Fill skewer as best as possible.
- Place skewers on grill. Rotate as needed to prevent flare ups. Cook until the chicken reaches 165F internal.
- Once chicken is close to done, preheat your reserve marinade and baste over the top of the chicken. Once chicken is done, pull and let rest for 2-3 minutes.
- Top chicken with chopped cilantro and lemon juice. Slice and enjoy!
.
.
.

Charcoal from @cowboycharcoal
Skewers from @superskewers
.
.
.

.

#ad Maple Guinness BBQ Pork Ribs are on the smoker today! Getting the crew together to watch the game? Try these bbq pork ribs out! They are the right call for your smoker. Click the link in my bio or visit my website (overthefirecooking.com) for more. Slainte! 🍻 🔥 🏈

Cheesy Steak Quesadilla for the start of the week! 🥩🧀🌶 🔥
.
Start your week right with this easy and fun recipe! We love steak AND we love quesadillas, so today’s recipe combines the two for the best of both worlds. You know what they say… the secret’s in the sauce 🤫 so we’re letting you in on our secret to a great quesadilla: the Chipotle Lime Mayo sauce. Drizzle that bad boy on top along with some jalapeños, red onion, cilantro and massive amounts of cheese. YUM! Cheers! Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/cheesy-steak-quesadilla/ 👍 🔥

Marinated Steak with Thai Chili Sauce for a quick dinner 🥩 🌶 🌿 🔥
.
We are back at it again over the fire, but this time with some Marinated Steak with Thai Chili Sauce. I am usually pulled towards South American and Latin American cuisine; but after going to a Thai restaurant and having some of their steak sauce, I knew that I needed it in my life. Grabbed myself a whole flap steak (yes, that is its real name) and all the ingredients needed to make this at home. This is a quick and simple cook that can be made over any grill! Find the recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/marinated-steak-with-thai-chili-sauce/ 🍻 👍

Pineapple Sriracha Shrimp Bowls that taste even better than they look! 🦐🍍🔥
.
Pineapple Sriracha Shrimp Bowls for the perfect sweet, spicy tang we all know and love. My good friends at @oklahomajoes just dropped a new grill, the Blackjack Kettle Charcoal Grill, which gave me the perfect opportunity to throw down on some shrimp bowls. I made a quick pineapple marinade for these shrimp and completed the meal with sriracha mayo and cilantro lime rice. Throw it all in a pineapple bowl for that extra wow factor. Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/pineapple-sriracha-shrimp-bowls/

node.text:
Whole Lobster grilled & poached in a Citrus Herb Butter over the fiyah! 🦞 🍋 🌿 🔥
.
Throwback to when I got some fresh lobster directly from Maine. I did not waste anytime cooking up a lobster recipe with these Whole Lobsters in a Citrus Herb Butter! I grilled them over the fire for about 3 minutes per side. Started meat side down then flipped them over to the shell side. Had a skillet full of a citrus herb butter sauce that I basically drenched over the lobster so that they poached inside their shell full of sauce. This was such a delicious recipe. Try it out asap! Also, find more of my recipes & rubs by clicking the link in my bio or visiting here: www.overthefirecooking.com! 🍻👍
.
.
.
Lobster:
- 2 Whole Lobster, split lengthwise & cleaned
- Sea Salt
- Black Pepper
- Oil
.
Butter:
- 1.5 sticks of Butter
- 2 tbsp of Parsley, chopped
- 2 tbsp of Cilantro, chopped
- 4 Garlic Cloves, chopped
- 1 tbsp of Scallions, chopped
- 1 tsp of Serrano Peppers, chopped
- 1 Lemon, juiced
- 1 Lime, juiced
.
.
Instructions:
1. Lather lobster with oil on meat and season using sea salt and black pepper. Set in fridge until ready to grill
2. Preheat your grill to a medium-high temperature (about 350F) for direct cooking.
3. Add a skillet to the grill and mix all ingredients for butter in it. Let melt and sizzle over fire for 1 minute.
4. Add your lobster tails, meat side down, to the grill and cook for about 3 minutes per side. Flip lobster over and top with butter sauce. Let cook for an additional 3 minutes or until it reaches 135F internal.
5. Once done, pull lobster off and let rest for 1 minute. Top with leftover butter sauce if desired, and enjoy!
.
.
.

node.text:
Beer Battered Fish on a Stick for a fun and delicious recipe! 🐟🍣🔥
Beer Battered Fish on a Stick is our grown up version of fish sticks. When a good  friend offers to share some freshly caught fish with you, you donʼt turn down that  offer. A Tennessee lager and some of my very own Chipotle Garlic seasoning were  the two MVP ingredients to the batter for this fried fish. Finish it off with a bit of  homemade chipotle sauce, jalapeños and chile crunch for the most delicious fish  sticks. Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/beer batter-fish-on-a-stick/ 🍻👍
. 
. 
#overthefirecooking

Roasted Chicken Trompo for perfect, juicy and delicious chicken! 🍗🥙🔥
.
Roasted Chicken Trompo for some delicious tzatziki pita pockets! The best way to level up any meal is by packing it full of some amazing protein. Call me biased, but I’ve found that the best proteins are cooked over an open flame. Inspired by Shawarma, we start by marinating some chicken so I can cook it on a vertical spit and turn it into an incredibly delicious and nutritious meal. Don’t save this one for later, go ahead and try it now! Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/roasted-chicken-trompo/ 🍻 👍

Smoked and Fried Sticky Wings are perfect for anytime! 🍗 🍯 🔥
.
I have been on a quest to make the most delicious chicken wings imaginable, and I think I might have found them. These Smoked and Fried Sticky Wings combine the smokiness from the @oklahomajoes Highland offset smoker, crispiness from frying and the sweet after taste of local honey. Delicious, simple and ready to be made in your backyard. Try out this recipe by clicking the link in my bio or visiting my blog: overthefirecooking.com 🍻 👍
.
